# Format-agnostic documentation

**Critical rule.** When editing related files, if you notice existing code or docs that violate this rule — even outside your current task — **flag it to the user as a high concern** before or alongside your main work. Do not silently ignore, copy the pattern, or defer without mention.

The internal data model and feature docs describe **our** codeplug — not any single vendor CPS. OpenGD77 is **one** import/export format among several (DM32, qDMR, CHIRP, native YAML).

## Internal model docs (`docs/features/data-model/`)

- Describe entities, fields, and internal UUID relationships.
- Point wire-format mapping to **[import/export](../../docs/features/import-export/README.md)** and per-format reference docs — not OpenGD77 alone.
- Radio caps and truncation belong in format/reference docs and export adapters, not internal-model docs.

## Unacceptable

- "Wire-format column detail lives in the [OpenGD77 reference](…)" — implies OpenGD77 is the only external model.
- "Wire-column mappings for every field above live in the [OpenGD77 reference](…)" — same.
- "Import an OpenGD77 export on the home page" as the **only** way to get test data — implies OpenGD77 is the only format.

## Acceptable

- "CSVs are mapped by the import/export layer (e.g. OpenGD77 → internal format)."
- "Import any supported CPS export (OpenGD77, DM32, …) or start a blank project."
- "See [OpenGD77 reference](../../docs/reference/opengd77/README.md) for OpenGD77 column mapping" — scoped to that format.
- "Known vendor leakage: wire-name FKs in validation — migrate to id-based refs."
- Documenting approved leakage fields (`vendorExtras`, planned `opengd77Extras`).

## Quick check

Before linking to `docs/reference/opengd77/`, ask: is this sentence about **OpenGD77 specifically**, or about **all** external formats? If the latter, link import/export docs or list formats explicitly.
